### Register user
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/register/
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "yousef",
    "email": "yousef@example.com",
    "password": "123456"
}

### Obtain JWT tokens
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/login/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "yousef",
  "password": "123456"
}

### Refresh token
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/users/token/refresh/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh": "PUT_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### List stocks (public/read)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/stocks/

### Create stock (admin only)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/stocks/
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "symbol": "AAPL",
  "name": "Apple Inc.",
  "exchange": "NASDAQ"
}

### List alerts (auth user)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/alerts/
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>

### Create alert (auth user)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/alerts/
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "stock": 1,
  "comparator": "gt",
  "threshold": "200.00",
  "duration": null
}

### List alert logs (owner or staff)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/alertlogs/
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>

### Create alert log (if API allows)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/alertlogs/
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "alert": 1,
  "price_at_trigger": "210.00",
  "message": "manual test"
}
